573
01:08:51.471 --> 01:08:53.013
I mean...

574
01:08:53.139 --> 01:08:55.547
It's... really good.

575
01:08:57.311 --> 01:08:59.932
I gotta get some air. I'm sorry.

576
01:09:00.481 --> 01:09:02.853
Excuse me for a moment.

577
01:09:04.735 --> 01:09:06.775
I'm sorry.

578
01:09:08.864 --> 01:09:10.904
We need to talk.

579
01:09:13.243 --> 01:09:16.161
Something's wrong. 
I can feel it.

580
01:09:16.288 --> 01:09:19.242
I've been trying to call
for three days. There's no answer.


581
01:09:19.375 --> 01:09:22.709
- She could be away.
- Yeah. She could be in trouble, too.


582
01:09:22.837 --> 01:09:25.755
- I gotta go back there.
- Listen to me.


583
01:09:27.259 --> 01:09:30.841
There's a door to the mystical,
and you've just walked through it.


584
01:09:30.971 --> 01:09:35.716
Right now, you are very vulnerable.
I wouldn't go back to Haiti now.


585
01:09:35.850 --> 01:09:39.931
You'd be a grade-school boy
in a world of Nobel Prize winners.


586
01:09:40.063 --> 01:09:43.182
I'd stay as far away
from Haiti as I could.


587
01:10:03.169 --> 01:10:07.499
What you have done is a major
breakthrough. It's quite mind-boggling.


588
01:10:08.466 --> 01:10:12.845
The only thing I don't understand
is how did Christophe Durand survive?


589
01:10:12.972 --> 01:10:15.048
How was he able to speak?

590
01:10:16.017 --> 01:10:17.475
Alex?

591
01:10:17.602 --> 01:10:22.678
Well, as far as we can tell,
somehow, I don't know how...


592
01:10:22.815 --> 01:10:27.062
someone dug him outta the grave
so no brain damage occurred.


593
01:10:39.165 --> 01:10:42.166
Is something wrong with your soup?

594
01:10:44.837 --> 01:10:47.921
No. No, it's all right, I...

595
01:10:49.508 --> 01:10:51.834
I'm not hungry.
- Albert?


596
01:10:52.386 --> 01:10:54.794
Dr Alan is finished with his soup.

597
01:10:56.724 --> 01:10:59.096
Perhaps monsieur would like
some salad instead?


598
01:10:59.226 --> 01:11:01.635
No, I, uh...

599
01:11:01.772 --> 01:11:04.689
I've been having
some stomach problems.


600
01:11:04.816 --> 01:11:09.194
Occupational hazard -
dysentery, botfly, malaria.


601
01:11:11.406 --> 01:11:13.814
A toast? A toast?

602
01:11:15.202 --> 01:11:17.111
To Dennis...

603
01:11:17.245 --> 01:11:20.946
to his adventures,
and to this marvelous discovery.


604
01:11:23.669 --> 01:11:26.623
He rang to a... a new...

605
01:11:27.339 --> 01:11:30.256
to a new...
- Debra? Sit down, Debra.


606
01:11:47.567 --> 01:11:52.943
<i>You're going to die.
You've been warned. You're going to die.</i>


607
01:11:53.825 --> 01:11:57.988
Debra, Debra.

608
01:12:29.485 --> 01:12:33.269
<i>He's gonna get to me,
wherever I am. I know that now.</i>


609
01:12:33.406 --> 01:12:36.075
<i>I've stolen his darkest and
most powerful secret.</i>


610
01:12:36.200 --> 01:12:40.530
<i>He'll want to get even and if he can't
get me, he'll go for Marielle.</i>


611
01:12:43.751 --> 01:12:46.076
Hey, I'm a US citizen!

612
01:12:46.253 --> 01:12:48.293
I'm a US citizen! Somebody!

613
01:12:53.802 --> 01:12:56.293
Hey, somebody!

614
01:12:59.934 --> 01:13:01.973
Lucien.

615
01:13:02.728 --> 01:13:06.347
<i>Lucien snatched me from under the
nose of the Tontons Macoutes.</i>


616
01:13:10.153 --> 01:13:13.568
<i>Marielle was safe. She was guarded
by his men at her clinic, he said.</i>


617
01:13:13.906 --> 01:13:17.690
<i>But for Mozart and me,
it was a different matter.</i>


618
01:13:29.046 --> 01:13:31.668
This will give you
some protection, that's all.


619
01:13:31.800 --> 01:13:35.169
Just like your
scientific objectivity.


620
01:13:36.680 --> 01:13:41.092
In this country, I haven't felt
protected by anything.


621
01:13:41.226 --> 01:13:44.096
<i>You don't know what
hasn't gotten to you.</i>


622
01:13:47.274 --> 01:13:49.599
I'm not afraid for myself.

623
01:13:49.734 --> 01:13:52.404
A good thing. Up.

624
01:14:05.208 --> 01:14:08.624
Remember, when the battle comes,
it won't be fought in the streets.


625
01:14:08.753 --> 01:14:12.039
It will be fought
in your mind, in your soul.


626
01:14:14.009 --> 01:14:17.378
Marielle was right. 
This must end.

627
01:14:18.096 --> 01:14:21.846
These people,
Peytraud, Duvalier...


628
01:14:22.893 --> 01:14:25.978
They're not Haiti,
they are mad dogs.


629
01:14:26.856 --> 01:14:28.895
The madness must stop.

630
01:14:29.900 --> 01:14:34.444
You're makin' a mistake. The president
and me, we are like this... like this.


631
01:14:46.460 --> 01:14:48.915
Something's wrong, isn't it?

632
01:15:00.097 --> 01:15:03.015
We are in our spirits' hands now,
you and I.


633
01:15:04.602 --> 01:15:07.852
Remember, whatever happens...

634
01:15:08.564 --> 01:15:10.889
